issue.title: Security provider support missing from legacy releases >22.0.0
issue.body:
Hi All,
I am trying to use kubernetes-client java on a FIPS enabled machine using the bouncy castle FIPS libraries. Commit #3590 allowed for bouncy castle FIPS support and loading of security providers but only seems to be included in release [22.0.0-legacy](https://github.com/kubernetes-client/java/blob/v22.0.0-legacy/util/src/main/java/io/kubernetes/client/util/SSLUtils.java#L52), and not [22.0.1-legacy](https://github.com/kubernetes-client/java/blob/v22.0.1-legacy/util/src/main/java/io/kubernetes/client/util/SSLUtils.java#L46) or [23.0.0-legacy](https://github.com/kubernetes-client/java/blob/v23.0.0-legacy/util/src/main/java/io/kubernetes/client/util/SSLUtils.java#L46). Breaking changes will be documented here, and deprecation warnings added to JS code where possible, at least one major version before the change is made.

Types of Breaking Changes

This document uses the following convention to categorize breaking changes:

  • API Changed: An API was changed in such a way that code that has not been updated is guaranteed to throw an exception.
  • Behavior Changed: The behavior of Electron has changed, but not in such a way that an exception will necessarily be thrown.

As a developer, I want to have a README that documents our Agile workflow so that new contributors understand how to use the repo.

    - Link issues to the project board  
    - Close issues via pull requests

- Given the README is updated,  
  When a new user follows the instructions,  
  Then they should be able to create their first issue successfully.
